ATT&CK
  A globally-accessible knowledge base of adversary tactics and techniques based on real-worls observations

CAR
  a knowledge base of analytics developed by MITRE based on the MITRE ATT&CKÂ® adversary model

MITRE ENGAGE
  a framework for planning and discussing adversary engagement operations that empowers you to engage your adversaries and achieve your cybersecurity goals.
  Considered an Adversary Engagement Approach
  Cyber Denial - prevention of the adversary's ability to conduct their operations

  Cyber Deception - intentionally planting artifacts to mislead the adversary

  5 categories
    Prepare the set of operational actions that will lead to your desired outcome (input)
    Expose adversaries when they trigger your deployed deception activities 
    Affect adversaries by performing actions that will have a negative impact on their operations
    Elicit information by observing the adversary and learn more about their modus operandi (TTPs)
    Understand the outcomes of the operational actions (output) 

D3FEND
  A knowledge graph of cybersecurity countermeasures
  Stands for Detection, Denial, and Disruption Framework Empowering Network Defense

ATT&CK Emulation Plans
  CTID - Organization (Center of Threat-Informed Defense) that consists of various companies and vendors that conduct research on cyber threats and their TTPs and share research to improve cyber defense

